ce:section.ce:para:
The toxicity effect of GQDs, GQDs-[Fe-Salen] and GQDs-[Fe-Salophen] on MCF7 cancer cells was evaluated in the concentration range of 0–250 μg/mL. Then the percentage of cell survival was measured by the MTT-assay method. Non-observation of toxicity of GQDs on MCF7 cancer cells confirms the biocompatibility of the substrate. The results show the high toxicity of GQDs-[Fe-Salen] and GQDs-[Fe-Salophen] compared to GQDs in the same concentration range. Also, it was found that cell death caused by GQDs-[Fe-Salen] and GQDs-[Fe-Salophen] is concentration-dependent (Fig. 12
                        ). The IC50 values (concentration of compounds that stop 50% growth of MCF7 cancer cells compared to control) for the synthesized compounds are reported in Table 1
                        . According to the obtained IC50 values, it can be concluded that GQDs-[Fe-Salen] has more anti-tumor activity compared to GQDs-[Fe-Salophen]. The low level of cytotoxicity of GQDs-[Fe-Salophen] compared to GQDs-[Fe-Salen] depends on factors such as intrinsic structure, cell uptake rate and cell interaction (Ansari and Kasiri, 2009).

The possibility of penetrating the synthesized samples (GQDs-[Fe-Salen] and GQDs-[Fe-Salophen]) into the cell was analyzed qualitatively and quantitatively. For this purpose, the samples were labeled with rhodamine. Then MCF7 cells were treated for 1 h and 4 h with samples labeled with rhodamine B. Fig. 15
                         shows the absorption of samples labeled with rhodamine B into MCF7 cells. Examination of the images in Fig. 15 shows that the images of GQDs-[Fe-Salen] have higher fluorescent intensity compared to the images of GQDs-[Fe-Salophen], this confirms the possibility of higher penetration of GQDs-[Fe-Salen] into MCF7 cells. Also, the images show that the penetration of the sample into the cell is completed within 4 h. To evaluate the results more accurately, the cellular absorption of the rhodamine B labeled samples was quantitatively measured using flow cytometry (Fig. 16
                        ). Untreated MCF7 cells were considered as control. The fluorescent intensity for GQDs-[Fe-Salen] and GQDs-[Fe-Salophen] was obtained as 16/89% and 10/01%, respectively. The fluorescent intensity has a direct relationship with the percentage of cell absorption. Therefore, it can be said that the cells treated with GQDs-[Fe-Salen] have more cellular uptake than GQDs-[Fe-Salophen], which is consistent with the MTT results.
